				\begin{document}$$T_{\mathrm{m}}$$\end{document}Tm(Conc.) is the temperature at which the temperature of nucleic acid reaches half of its maximum value [27]. It is known that the secondary structure can indeed cause inhibition of RNAi [34–36]. Also the secondary structure of RNAi can be involved in the RISC cleavage. That is why predicting secondary structures in order to guide selection of sites for RNAi targeting is more important [28]. Secondary structures of RNAi provide a convenient and computationally tractable estimation not only to structures but also to the thermodynamics of RNA–RNA interaction. UNAfold predicts the most stable secondary structure of an oligonucleotide by minimizing folding free energy. The folded structures are predicted at the specified temperature which is 37 °C. The secondary structures of siRNA and miRNA are shown in Figs. 1a–e, 2a–c and 3. After analysis of all siRNA and miRNA, finally five siRNA and four miRNA pass all barriers of effectiveness and those are worthy to fight against MERS-CoV. RNA interference (RNAi) is a novel regulatory and powerful silencing approach for molecular therapeutics [37]. Though both siRNA and miRNA have novel function for gene silencing, siRNA is comparatively better than miRNA due to its sequence specificity with targets and easier insertion techniques (via nano-particle, lipid based transfection, etc.) into the cell. Imbued by the mechanism and suitability of RNAi, scientists and pharmaceuticals are working to use it as next-generation therapeutics. To treat a wide variety of disease, RNAi technology is the riding lamp to researchers. Current discoveries on miRNAs’ involvement in cancer suggest that RNA inhibition can be used as an advanced mean for treating cancer patients [38]. miRNA-based therapeutics are also in consideration for the treatment of cardiovascular disorders [39].







With RNAi technology, it is possible to design a number of siRNA and miRNA molecules for silencing of substantial genes in numerous biological systems. Their connections with target can also be calculated computationally. Hence, in our study five siRNA and four miRNA molecules were predicted against ORF1ab gene of different strains of MERS-CoV as effective aspirant using computational approaches.
These molecules may be a key to a novel antiviral therapy against MERS-CoV. This research will open the milestone corridor in MERS therapy. The consequence of this study would also afford a foundation to the researchers and pharmaceutical industry to advance antiviral therapeutics at genomic level.
